    "actor_description": "It lands softly: done. The push in my chest eases and my focus stops gripping so hard, like I can finally put the weight down. I feel a small, private solidness—nothing flashy, just the sense that I handled it. The energy drains out in a good way, leaving me steadier than before.",
    "description_text": "{actor} exhales and visibly downshifts—shoulders loosening, gaze no longer hunting for the next step. Their posture reads quietly satisfied, as if effort has been set aside and something has clicked into place.",
